-- Giggs Joins Richards, Bellamy on British Olympic Soccer Squad
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2012-07-02T14:17:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-02/giggs-joins-richards-bellamy-on-british-olympic-soccer-squad.html
Manchester United ’s Tom Cleverley and
 Ryan Giggs  will join Liverpool’s  Craig Bellamy  and Manchester
City’s Micah Richards on Britain’s Olympic soccer team.  Giggs, Bellamy and Richards are the squad’s three players
over 23-years-old, with the rest of the players being younger,
according to an e-mailed statement from local Olympic
organizers.  Cleverley and Arsenal’s  Aaron Ramsey  will help form
the midfield.  Britain hasn’t fielded a team with players recruited from
all the home nations -- England,  Wales , Scotland and  Northern
Ireland  -- for men’s soccer since the 1960  Olympic Games  in
Rome, where the team finished third in its group.  The squad will play its first match against Senegal at
United’s Old Trafford on July 26th.  The squad:  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
